definitions.definition: An action or act ; something that is done.
examples: One small deed can have one stour effect or more.

definitions.definition: A brave or noteworthy action; a feat or exploit .
Action or fact, as opposed to rhetoric or deliberation.
examples: I have fulfilled my promise in word and in deed .

definitions.definition: A legal instrument that is executed under seal or before a witness ; sometimes required for certain legal activities, such as the transfer of certain kinds of property .

subdefinitions.definition: The legal title to real estate; ownership .
examples: I inherited the deed to the house.
